28/11/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Leaders of four largest political parties -- the VMRO-DPMNE's Nikola Gruevski, the Democratic Party of Albanians' Arben Xhaferri, the Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia's Radmila Sekerinska and the Democratic Union for Integration's Ali Ahmeti -- met on Monday (November 27th) for the first direct dialogue between the ruling parties and the opposition since the summer elections.
The meeting was initiated by the US and EU ambassadors to Macedonia, Gillian Milovanovic and Erwan Fouere, who insist consensus regarding the EU and NATO reform agenda is crucial to the country's integration efforts.
Party leaders agreed to meet again in 12 days to continue discussions.
(Vecer - 28/11/06;
MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 27/11/06)
